            "video_autoplay": false,
            "heading": "Vernon Distillery",
            "heading_size": "h1",
            "text": "<p>Home to North America’s tallest copper pot still, our original flagship distillery was relocated and redesigned in early 2015. Witness first-hand the magic of craft distilling in our 16,000 sq. ft. production facility where the gleaming copper-pots will immediately captivate as you walk through the door.<br/><br/>The sprawling tasting area was built to honour the Okanagan’s rich tree-fruit history. You’ll be greeted with a wall-size photograph of a crew picking apples at the Coldstream ranch in 1918 – look beyond to see a moonshiner shack motif built with reclaimed beams, originally from the long demolished Fruit Union packinghouse where Dyck family ancestors once worked.<br/><br/>Experience selections from our full product lineup at our 27-foot tasting bar. Even after multiple visits, you’ll always find something new with well over 40 award-winning products to choose from – each hand crafted with the guarantee that no artificial flavouring, colouring or essences have been added.<br/></p>",
